        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I'm currently using extended range and extended affliction.  The extended affliction of course can't be beat.  Anytime you can extend the duration and therefore the damage of a DoT it is a good thing.  Extended range is okay but for the most part you can do without it.  It would probably be a good idea to keep a ER item in your pack for those times when it would be really useful but I wouldn't make great efforts to build my gear around this effect. </P><P>I would think that mana efficiency, extended affliction and spell haste would be the three best for necros. Unless you are planning on taking on a mob that would require the chain casting of pets I can't see that reanimation haste is really all that special but that is just me.</P><P> </font></td>
